✅ Scenario 1 — Create EC2 only if environment is “prod”

You have a variable environment.
If prod → launch 2 EC2 instances
If dev → launch 0 EC2 instances

Requirement: Use an if condition to control count.

✅ Scenario 2 — Choose instance type based on environment

If environment = "prod" → use t3.large
Else → use t3.micro

Use an if expression inside a variable or resource.

✅ Scenario 3 — Enable S3 versioning only in prod

If prod → versioning = "Enabled"
Else → versioning = "Suspended"

✅ Scenario 4 — Add a tag only if is_enabled = true

If is_enabled = true → add tag "Monitoring" = "Enabled"
Else → no tag should be created.

✅ Scenario 5 — Create IAM user only if create_user = true

Variable: create_user.
If true → create IAM user
If false → skip the resource using count.